channel.title: All the noobs are on mopar?
channel.description: Seems like theres 5000 people that have no idea what they're doing, and are begging for help... but if you go to a different community you find pros. Was moparscape made before or after other communities?

item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

luke rowland:

sadface

Mute this kid already.

Look, every community is going to have the greats and the noobs. Most of the “legends” have passed (graham), but still every now and then a truely smart person comes and makes a great advancement.

It’s not that they’re all “noobs”, they just saw success from those few great servers and just figured it would be good to use that base. When Delta came out, people where really impressed, and since then people have just been trying to copy the success, for better or worse (money).

Every community will have flaws, but no community has more then 20% of raw intelligence.
